'''''Algonquin''''' is a 2014 Canadian drama film written and directed by Jonathan Hayes.

==Plot==
Leif ([[Nicholas Campbell]]), a travel writer whose career has declined, visits his son Jake ([[Mark Rendall]]). The father plans to produce a book about [[Algonquin Park]] and invites his son to join him in its writing.<ref name=GM /> Leif also meets up with Rita ([[Sheila McCarthy]]), his former wife and Jake's mother.<ref name=CC>{{cite news | url=http://www.canada.com/entertainment/movie-guide/Movie+review+Algonquin+fractured+drama+lovely+setting/9797019/story.html | title=Movie review: Algonquin a fractured drama in a lovely setting | first=Jay | last=Stone | publisher=Postmedia News | date=1 May 2014 | accessdate=1 May 2014 }}</ref> Matters are complicated when they are joined by Carmen ([[Victoria Sanchez (actress)|Victoria Sanchez]]), Leif's young romantic partner, and her son Iggy ([[Michael Levinson]]).<ref name=TS>{{cite news | url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2014/04/10/algonquin_paddles_through_familys_twist_and_turns_review.html | title=Algonquin paddles through family's twist and turns: review | first=Linda | last=Barnard | newspaper=Toronto Star | date=10 April 2014 | accessdate=1 May 2014 }} {{rating|2.5|4}}</ref> Leif and Jake then proceed with a canoe trip through Algonquin Park to find a particular horseshoe.<ref name=CC /><ref name=TS /><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.actratoronto.com/tip-feature-playing-in-toronto/ | title=TiP Feature Playing in Toronto | date=9 April 2014 | publisher=ACTRA Toronto | accessdate=1 May 2014 }}</ref>

