==Production==
''Algonquin'' marks the first time that Hayes has written and directed a feature film.<ref name=GM>{{cite news | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/film/film-reviews/algonquin-adrift-in-the-wilderness-typically-canadian/article17924218/ | title=Algonquin: Adrift in the wilderness, typically Canadian  | first=Liam | last=Lacey | newspaper=The Globe and Mail | date=11 April 2014 | accessdate=1 May 2014 }} {{rating|2.5|4}}</ref>

==Release==
The film was first screened at the [[Montreal World Film Festival]] on 24 August 2013.<ref name=WFF>{{cite web | url=http://www.ffm-montreal.org/en/163-en_algonquin.html | title=Algonquin | publisher=Festival des Films du Monde / World Film Festival | accessdate=1 May 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502073128/http://www.ffm-montreal.org/en/163-en_algonquin.html | archive-date=2 May 2014 | dead-url=yes | df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=OC1>{{cite news | url=https://ottawacitizen.com/entertainment/movie-guide/Canadian+Father+film+iconic+Algonquin+Park/9792751/story.html | title=All Canadian: Father-son film set in iconic Algonquin Park | first=Peter | last=Robb | newspaper=Ottawa Citizen | date=1 May 2014 | accessdate=1 May 2014 }}</ref>

